content.description: The Voyeur is the 4th bolted route from the right and the right of the two longer bolted routes. Face climb on good rock to the obvious pod/hueco. Swing out on steep rock into the bottom of the hueco, turn the lip(crux)and climb to the anchors.
Bouldery start from the deck using a nice flake feature leads to easier clipping above. Well bolted and safe.
content.location:
Left most bolted route on the farthest left part of the wall, which is a scramble up to the "upper" wall. Identified easily by the large vertical fin/flake about 8 feet off the deck.

If you are looking at the guide, its wrong. Scramble up the gully from the tall walls and you will find #926-929    930-932 are in the approach gully.

content.description: Similar start as Getty Up- "Would be bouldering" is actually some thoughtful and delicate moves to get established. Some great knife edge sidepulls and long reaches await you above! Very fun for the area.
content.protection: 8 bolts, Shares closed anchors with Cromag and Celibate Rifle.
content.location: Third Bolted line on the Upper Dude. Immediately left of the hard line Cromag.

content.description: Redneck is located on the far right side of the crag. This climb starts on the beautiful red face on good edges and continues up through various features to the anchor.
content.protection: 7 bolts, closed cold shut anchor shared with City Slickers and Redneck.

content.location: Chimney that sits between The Flake route and the overhanging Hidden Agenda. Can be identified by the white marking oozing from the lowest point in the chimney.

climbs.name: Hidden Agenda
climbs.fa: Jack Marshall,  Sam Owings, Howie Stern

content.description: Hidden Agenda is the left most bolted route on the lower/right formation. Start face climbing on good rock up to a difficult steep move/blind reach to the left to gain a shallow hueco on the overhanging blunt arete. Steep moves out of the hueco (crux) are are made using a inobvious kneebar (Hidden Agenda), continue up steep, difficult climbing to some tricky moves right to get to lower angle rock and easier climbing to the anchors.
Hard and delicate moves from the ground that could be confused for a bouldery start lead to technical hands above. Easier above but still not "That" easy
content.protection: Bolts, shares two closed shuts with "The Roundup"
content.location: Second bolted line on the wall. Move over-hanging and thinner start.

content.description: Attention grabbing start off the deck, featuring thin crimpy holds that demand balance to get established. The fall would not be good. One could stand on the opposing boulder to pre-clip the first hanger.. I suppose.  Up higher you will find fun vertical cracks with side-pulls and edging. Overall a fun pitch.
content.location: Center climb on the "slab" face area of the Dude. Starts / belays from about halfway up the gully from Hidden agenda. Has some older bolts, pained reddish.

content.description: A committing move from the gully start gets you high over the floor and the  gains you the first bolt. Don't biff! It will hurt. Follow the line to a blank face and decide if you will go hard or go home. Harder moves to the left would warrant a harder 10 grade, or stick to the right to stay 10a.
content.protection: Bolts, shares anchors with Funny Face.
content.location: Find the main wall with under "Hidden Agenda" and "Voyer" To the left starts an upward gully scramble that leads to the Upper Ranch. This climb starts about 10 feet up the gully and can be identified by low bolts and obvious juggy low holds that will put you into an airy stance. If you are looking at page 240 in the Mayr guide...Dont. ( based on that topo, you would be looking at #928, 929 being the "Offwith Chimney"

content.description: Curly starts 10' left of Redneck, climb the slab up to steeper climbing past bolts and tricky climbing to join Redneck for the last few bolts to a chain anchor.
content.protection: bolts, shared anchor with City Slickers and Redneck.

content.description: Hardest route on the wall. Starts with some powerful moves off the deck, to a tricky first clip which is quite high. Passing the first clip is the crux but still offers strenuous climbing to the second clip where the climbing gets a bit easier... probably 10d in the upper section
content.protection: Bolts, shares anchors with "Roughneck" on the left and "Celibate Rifle" on the right.
content.location: 4th bolted line from the left. Starts about 5 feet right of the boulder that one must down climb to access the upper wall.

content.description: City Slickers is the 3rd route from the right. Climb the slab past a bolt to the obvious crack. Climb the crack and move right(crux)to face climbing to the anchor.
content.protection: bolts, shares anchor with Curly and Redneck

content.description: Start on top of the boulder, reaching for a "huecoey flake" from the left side of the arete to gain the first bolt and easier climbing to the face.
content.location: Right side of the "upper" wall section. Bolts will appear to be on the face/slab. To the right of "Cromag" and to the left of "Funny Face"11a.
